snapFPlanIO(25.10)                                          snapFPlanIO(25.10)

Name
       snapFPlanIO - Snaps I/O cells to a user-defined grid

Syntax
        snapFPlanIO

       [-help]

       [-selected]

       [-userGrid | -toIoRow [-overlapRowOnly]]

       Snaps  I/O cells to a user-defined grid. Use this command after import-
       ing the design.

       Note: You can specify the user-defined grid in the Preferences - Floor-
       plan form in the View Menu of the Innovus GUI.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each snapFPlanIO parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man snapFPlanIO

       -overlapRowOnly
              Snaps  the  I/O cell only onto an overlapping I/O row. If an I/O
              row is not found, the command is not executed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -selected
              Applies to the selected I/Os only.

              Default: snaps to all I/O cells.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -toIoRow
              Snaps the I/O cell onto an overlapping I/O row first. If an  I/O
              row is not found, places the I/O cell in any row having the same
              site.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -userGrid
              Specifies the snapping of I/O pads to user-defined grids.

              Default: snaps I/O to manufacture grid.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

